      "writtenOn": "2019-06-19T06:31:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "bool stillRunning \u003d false;\n{\n    AutoLock lock(mLock);\n    mPlayConfig \u003d config;\n    stillRunning \u003d mRunning;\n}\n\nif (!stillRunning) {\n   // Reset the worker thread out of the lock, because destroying the previous thread may take the lock.\n   mWorkerThread.reset(new base::FunctorThread([this]() { workerThreadFunc(); }));\n\n   mRunning \u003d true;\n   mWorkerThread-\u003estart();\n}\n\n\nIt\u0027s safe to call mWorkerThread-\u003estart() under the lock.  However, I think we need to move the mRunning state into this function to prevent the following sequence:\n\nT1: start(PlayConfig) with running\u003dfalse\nT2 created, but not started\nT1: start(PlayConfig) with running\u003dfalse (again)\nT1: blocks and waits for T2 to complete before creating T3",
